### 3.2 IMU prefilter path (driver вҶ’ EKF)

`VehicleIMU` (`src/modules/sensors/vehicle_imu/`) subscribes to `sensor_accel`/`sensor_gyro`, applies **calibration** (scale/offset/rotation) and **integrates** over the `IMU_INTEG_RATE` window (default 200 Hz) with a coning-corrected integrator, publishing `vehicle_imu.{delta_angle, delta_velocity}` (+ their `dt`). **No low-pass or notch filter is applied on this path** вҖ” EKF2 does its own internal handling. (The notched/LPF'd `vehicle_angular_velocity` / `vehicle_acceleration` topics are for the *rate/attitude/position controllers*, not the estimator вҖ” see the IMU note.)

The integrated delta form is what the strapdown prediction (В§5.1) consumes directly:

```
delta_angle  вүҲ вҲ« Пү_body dt     (rad, body frame, over the integration window)
delta_velocity вүҲ вҲ« a_body dt   (m/s, body frame, gravity included)
```

### 3.3 Time alignment, down-sampling & buffering

Every non-IMU sample is **time-shifted backward** before being buffered so its timestamp lands on the EKF's delayed fusion horizon (`estimator_interface.cpp:123/159/238`):

```
t_buffer = t_sample вҲ’ EKF2_<S>_DELAYВ·1e3[Вөs] вҲ’ _dt_ekf_avgВ·5e5      (the В·5e5 = ВҪ EKF step, in Вөs)
```

A `_min_obs_interval_us = (t_imu_now вҲ’ _time_delayed_us)/(_obs_buffer_length вҲ’ 1)` rate-limits each buffer so no sample is overwritten before the horizon reaches it (`:97`).

The **IMU down-sampler** (`imu_down_sampler.cpp:13`) accumulates fast IMU samples to the filter rate set by `EKF2_PREDICT_US` (10 000 Вөs вҶ’ 100 Hz):

```
ОҙОё_acc(quat) = ОҙОё_acc вҠ— О”q(ОҙОё_new)                 # quaternion accumulation of delta angle
Оҙv_acc       = R(О”q)вҒ»В№В·Оҙv_acc + ВҪ(Оҙv_new + R(О”q)вҒ»В№В·Оҙv_new)   # rotate forward, trapezoidal
trigger when  (#samples вүҘ _required_samples & ОҙОё_dt > _min_dt_s)  OR  ОҙОё_dt > _target_dt_s
```

On trigger the sample is pushed to `_imu_buffer`; `_time_delayed_us = _imu_buffer.get_oldest().time_us` is the **fusion horizon**. `_dt_ekf_avg` is the slewed average step used by both prediction steps (`ekf.cpp:293`). The **output predictor** (В§7.1) instead runs on *every* full-rate IMU sample inside `setIMUData()` (`estimator_interface.cpp:83`).

