## 4. The 24-state vector

`stateSample` (`common.h:269`); symbolic names from the SymForce derivation `EKF/python/ekf_derivation/derivation.py:39`. Covariance `P` is a 24Г—24 symmetric matrix.

| Idx | Symbol | `stateSample` member | Meaning | Units |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| 0вҖ“3 | `qw qx qy qz` | `quat_nominal` | rotation **body вҶ’ earth** (NED) | вҖ“ |
| 4вҖ“6 | `vx vy vz` | `vel` | velocity, earth NED | m/s |
| 7вҖ“9 | `px py pz` | `pos` | position, earth NED (z = down) | m |
| 10вҖ“12 | `d_ang_bx/by/bz` | `delta_ang_bias` | **delta-angle** (gyro) bias | rad |
| 13вҖ“15 | `d_vel_bx/by/bz` | `delta_vel_bias` | **delta-velocity** (accel) bias | m/s |
| 16вҖ“18 | `ix iy iz` | `mag_I` | earth magnetic field, NED | gauss |
| 19вҖ“21 | `ibx iby ibz` | `mag_B` | magnetometer bias, body | gauss |
| 22вҖ“23 | `wx wy` | `wind_vel` | horizontal wind, earth NE | m/s |

> **Delta biases, not rate biases.** States 10вҖ“15 are biases on the *integrated* IMU increments over one sample, so the equivalent rate/accel bias is `delta_ang_bias / Оҙt` and `delta_vel_bias / Оҙt`. The same `K`-slice mapping is used everywhere by `Ekf::fuse` (`ekf_helper.cpp:789`): `q -= K[0:4]В·e`, `v -= K[4:7]В·e`, `p -= K[7:10]В·e`, `ОҙОё_b -= K[10:13]В·e`, `Оҙv_b -= K[13:16]В·e`, `mag_I -= K[16:19]В·e`, `mag_B -= K[19:22]В·e`, `wind -= K[22:24]В·e`.

`P(9,9)` is the vertical-position variance, `P(4..6,В·)` the velocity block, etc. вҖ” the indices above *are* the covariance indices.

