## 5. EKF update cycle

![EKF2 update cycle and R/Q hooks](ekf2_estimator_pipeline_2026-05-25_cycle.svg)

`Ekf::update()` (`ekf.cpp:158`) runs once per down-sampled IMU sample, in this order: **predictCovariance вҶ’ predictState вҶ’ controlFusionModes вҶ’ correctOutputStates**.

### 5.1 State prediction вҖ” strapdown INS (`predictState`, `ekf.cpp:253`)

```
ОҙОё_corr = ОҙОё вҲ’ ОҙОё_b вҲ’ RбөҖВ·Пү_earthВ·Оҙt          # gyro bias + earth-rotation removed   (:257-260)
q       вҶҗ (q вҠ— О”q(ОҙОё_corr)).normalized()      # quaternion propagation               (:262-265)
R_eb    = DCM(q)
Оҙv_corr = Оҙv вҲ’ Оҙv_b
v       вҶҗ v + R_ebВ·Оҙv_corr                     # specific-force increment, earth frame (:271-277)
v(2)    вҶҗ v(2) + gВ·Оҙt          (g = +9.80665, NED down)                                (:280)
p       вҶҗ p + ВҪ(v_old + v)В·Оҙt                  # trapezoidal position                  (:283)
_dt_ekf_avg вҶҗ 0.99В·_dt_ekf_avg + 0.01В·clamp(ВҪ(ОҙОё_dt+Оҙv_dt))                            (:288-293)
```

Bias states are **unchanged** by prediction вҖ” they only move during fusion. The symbolic form is `derivation.py:94-96` (`q_new = q вҠ— [1, ВҪОҙОё_true]`, `v_new = v + RВ·Оҙv_true + gВ·dt`, `p_new = p + vВ·dt`).

### 5.2 Covariance prediction & process noise Q (`predictCovariance`, `covariance.cpp:102`)

The propagation is the standard EKF form, generated symbolically by SymForce and compiled into `predict_covariance.h` (`sym::PredictCovariance(...)`, вҖңTotal ops: 2887вҖқ):

```
P вҶҗ AВ·PВ·AбөҖ + GВ·var_uВ·GбөҖ
A = вҲӮx_new/вҲӮx  (24Г—24 state Jacobian)      G = вҲӮx_new/вҲӮ[Оҙv,ОҙОё]  (noise Jacobian)
var_u = diag(Оҙv_varГ—3 , ОҙОё_varГ—3)          dt = _dt_ekf_avg
ОҙОё_var = (dtВ·gyro_noise)ВІ                  Оҙv_var(i) = (dtВ·accel_noise)ВІ  [or BADACC if clipping/bad]
```

The **stationary** states get a process-noise diagonal added on top (`covariance.cpp:227-241`):

| States | Пғ (process) | Param (default) | Gating |
|---|---|---|---|
| 10вҖ“12 ОҙОё-bias | `dtВІВ·gyro_bias_p_noise` | `EKF2_GYR_B_NOISE` 1.0e-3 | frozen if `!ImuCtrl::GyroBias` |
| 13вҖ“15 Оҙv-bias | `dtВІВ·accel_bias_p_noise` | `EKF2_ACC_B_NOISE` 3.0e-3 | frozen if `!AccelBias` вҲҘ high-manoeuvre вҲҘ bad-accel вҲҘ axis clipping вҲҘ not observable |
| 16вҖ“18 mag_I | `dtВ·mage_p_noise` | `EKF2_MAG_E_NOISE` 1.0e-3 | only if `mag_3D` & `ОЈP(16:18) < 0.1` |
| 19вҖ“21 mag_B | `dtВ·magb_p_noise` | `EKF2_MAG_B_NOISE` 1.0e-4 | only if `mag_3D` & `ОЈP(19:21) < 0.1` |
| 22вҖ“23 wind | `[wind_vel_nsdВ·(1+0.5В·|бёЈ_lpf|)]ВІВ·dt` | `EKF2_WIND_NSD` 1.0e-2 | only if `wind` & `ОЈP(22:23) < 1` |
| IMU ОҙОё in | `(dtВ·gyro_noise)ВІ` | `EKF2_GYR_NOISE` 1.5e-2 | via `G` |
| IMU Оҙv in | `(dtВ·accel_noise)ВІ` | `EKF2_ACC_NOISE` 3.5e-1 | via `G`; вҶ’ `BADACC_BIAS_PNOISE` on clip/bad |

**Bias inhibit** (`covariance.cpp:125-190`): when a gyro/accel-bias axis is unobservable or the vehicle is manoeuvring hard (`_ang_rate_magnitude_filt > acc_bias_learn_gyr_lim` вҲҘ `_accel_magnitude_filt > acc_bias_learn_acc_lim`), its variance is *frozen* (saved & restored) so the bias estimate cannot wander. Covariance symmetry/limits are enforced by `fixCovarianceErrors()`.

### 5.3 Generic measurement update

Each aiding source builds an `estimator_aid_source*_s` (innovation, variance, test ratio) then calls the shared update. For velocity/position/height this is the **sequential scalar** helper `fuseVelPosHeight()` (`vel_pos_fusion.cpp:193`); other sources use the analogous `measurementUpdate()`/`fuse()` path. The maths:

```
innov  = z вҲ’ h(x)                              # e.g. updateVerticalPositionAidSrcStatus: pos(2) вҲ’ obs
S      = HВ·PВ·HбөҖ + R                            # innovation variance  (obs_var floored at 0.01ВІ)
test   = innovВІ / (gateВІВ·S)        accept iff test < 1          # NIS outlier gate
K      = PВ·HбөҖ / S                              # Kalman gain  (for vel/pos H is a unit row вҶ’ K = P(:,sбөў)/S)
x      вҶҗ x вҲ’ KВ·innov                           # Ekf::fuse, ekf_helper.cpp:789
P      вҶҗ P вҲ’ KВ·HВ·P  ( = P вҲ’ KHP )              # then fixCovarianceErrors() + symmetry
```

For `fuseVelPosHeight` the observation index 0вҖ“5 maps to state index 4вҖ“9 (vN vE vD pN pE pD); a special case clamps (rather than rejects) vertical innovations when `bad_acc_vertical` is set, to ride out IMU clipping without destabilising height.

