### 6.2 Deep dives

**Velocity / position / height** (`vel_pos_fusion.cpp`). `H` is a unit row selecting one state, so the update is the scalar form of В§5.3 with `S = P(sбөў,sбөў) + R`. Observations are built by `updateVelocityAidSrcStatus` / `updateHorizontalPositionAidSrcStatus` / `updateVerticalPositionAidSrcStatus` (`:46-130`): `innov = state вҲ’ obs`, `innov_var = P(sбөў,sбөў) + max(0.01ВІ, obs_var)`. Height is special because several sensors can drive `p(2)`; see the dispatcher and bias estimators below.

**Magnetometer** (`mag_fusion.cpp`). 3-axis: `R_MAG = mag_noiseВІ`; the generated `ComputeMagInnovInnovVarAndHx` yields a **sparse** Jacobian over states `{q(0:3), mag_I(16:18), mag_B(19:21)}`; fused sequentially XвҶ’YвҶ’Z with per-axis covariance-conditioning checks. Heading-only mode uses `fuseYaw()` with `mag_heading_noise` and `EKF2_HDG_GATE`. Declination is constrained by `fuseDeclination()`. Mode selection (`EKF2_MAG_TYPE`, auto vs heading vs 3D) is in `mag_control.cpp`.

**GPS** (`gps_control.cpp:42`). Velocity obs variance `vel_var = max(sacc, gps_vel_noise)ВІ` with the **vertical component inflated** `Г—1.5ВІ` (`:91-92`); horizontal position `pos_noise = max(hacc, gps_pos_noise)`, **capped at `pos_noaid_noise`** when GPS is the only horizontal aid (`:103-109`). GPS *height* (when `EKF2_GPS_CTRL` has the VPOS bit) goes through the height dispatcher with its own bias estimator (`gnss_height_control.cpp`). Dual-antenna yaw via `gps_yaw_fusion.cpp`.

### 6.3 The specialised sources (one line each)

- **Airspeed** (`airspeed_fusion.cpp`) вҖ” fixed-wing; `h = вҖ–v вҲ’ windвҖ–`; observes velocity & wind; resets wind on first fusion; needs `EKF2_ARSP_THR > 0`.
- **Sideslip** (`sideslip_fusion.cpp`) вҖ” synthetic `ОІ = 0` assumption; `R = beta_noiseВІ`; fused ~every 150 ms; bootstraps/holds the wind states for fixed-wing.
- **Drag** (`drag_fusion.cpp`) вҖ” multirotor wind from body X/Y specific force using a bluff-body (`EKF2_BCOEF_*`) + rotor-momentum (`EKF2_MCOEF`) model; observes velocity & wind.
- **Optical flow** (`optflow_fusion.cpp`) вҖ” LOS angular rate vs `v_body/range` minus body rate; noise scaled by sensor quality; couples to the terrain estimate for range.
- **Range finder** (`range_height_control.cpp`, `sensor_range_finder.cpp`) вҖ” height-above-ground; `R = (range_noise + range_noise_scalerВ·range)ВІ`; `EKF2_RNG_CTRL` (0/1/2 = off/conditional/on); conditional aiding limited by `max_hagl_for_range_aid`, `max_vel_for_range_aid`, tilt; kinematic-consistency check.
- **External vision** (`ev_pos/vel/yaw/height_control.cpp`) вҖ” NED or FRD pos/vel/yaw/height; `EKF2_EV_CTRL` bitmask; frame conversion + lever arm; non-reference pos/height get bias estimators.
- **Gravity** (`gravity_fusion.cpp`) вҖ” tilt constraint from the accelerometer when `вҖ–aвҖ–вүҲg`; enabled by `EKF2_IMU_CTRL` GravityVector bit; useful before mag/GPS alignment.
- **Aux velocity** (`auxvel_fusion.cpp`) вҖ” generic external NE velocity (e.g. landing-target).
- **Zero-velocity / zero-yaw** (`zero_velocity_update.cpp`, `zero_innovation_heading_update.cpp`) вҖ” pseudo-measurements applied at rest to bound velocity/yaw drift and let accel-bias learn.
- **Fake position / height** (`fake_pos_control.cpp`, `fake_height_control.cpp`) вҖ” last-known constraints with `pos_noaid_noise` when no real aiding exists, preventing unbounded drift.

### 6.4 Height / position **bias estimators** (the non-reference reconciliation)

Several sources can supply height (or horizontal position); one is the **reference** and the others are reconciled to it through a scalar Kalman **bias** filter (`bias_estimator.cpp`, `height_bias_estimator.hpp`). Model (`bias_estimator.hpp`): `A=1`, `x[k+1]=x[k]+v`, `y=x+w`.

```
predict:  О”ПғВІ = _process_psdВ·dt;  if offset detected вҶ’ О”ПғВІ В·= 1000;  ПғВІ += О”ПғВІ; clamp[1e-8, ПғВІ_max]
fuse:     S = ПғВІ + max(0.01ВІ, R);  innov = z вҲ’ x;  K = ПғВІ/S
          if innovВІ/(gateВІВ·S) < 1:  x += KВ·innov;  ПғВІ вҲ’= KВ·ПғВІ
offset:   |LPF(signВ·test_ratio)| > 0.2  or persistent same-sign innovations (>10 s)
```

`_process_psd = (EKF2_*_BIAS_NSD)ВІ` with all four NSDs = 0.13 mВ·sвҒ»В№В·вҲҡHzвҒ»В№ (baro/gps/rng/ev). The **reference sensor's bias estimator is inert** вҖ” `HeightBiasEstimator::predict/fuseBias` are guarded by `(_sensor_ref != _sensor)` (`height_bias_estimator.hpp:57/64`), so the reference owns the datum and only the non-reference offsets are tracked. **Worked example:** `EKF2_HGT_REF=0` (baro reference) with GPS height enabled вҖ” baro's estimator is frozen, GPS gets a bias вүҲ (GPS-MSL) вҲ’ (baro-altitude). Full treatment in `ekf2_height_ref_baro_2026-05-21.*`.

### 6.5 EKFGSF_yaw вҖ” emergency yaw (`EKFGSF_yaw.cpp`)

A bank of *N* lightweight AHRS+EKF filters seeded at different yaw angles, weighted by a Gaussian-Sum likelihood from GPS-velocity consistency. When the main filter's yaw diverges (e.g. mag loss), the composite `_gsf_yaw` (if confident enough) is used to **reset** the main EKF yaw. Output is published as `yaw_estimator_status`.

