## 7. Outputs

### 7.1 Output predictor (`output_predictor.cpp`)

The EKF solution is at the *delayed* horizon; the output predictor produces the low-latency `now` solution the vehicle consumes. Two phases:

**Forward INS вҖ” `calculateOutputStates()` (`:168`, every full-rate IMU sample):**
```
ОҙОё_c = ОҙОё вҲ’ ОҙОё_b + _delta_angle_corr            # note the complementary correction term
q_o  вҶҗ (q_o вҠ— О”q(ОҙОё_c)).normalize()
Оҙv_e = R(q_o)В·(Оҙv вҲ’ Оҙv_b);  Оҙv_e(2) += gВ·Оҙt
v_o  вҶҗ v_o + Оҙv_e;  p_o вҶҗ p_o + ВҪ(v_o+v_o,prev)В·Оҙt     # trapezoidal
v_imu_rel = (ОҙОё_c/Оҙt) Г— imu_pos_body            # IMU lever-arm correction вҶ’ NED
```

**Complementary correction вҖ” `correctOutputStates()` (`:242`, once per EKF update):** push `_output_new` to a ring buffer, take the oldest (delayed) entry, and drive it toward the EKF state:
```
q_err = (q_ekfвҒ»В№ вҠ— q_o,delayed).normalize();  Оҙa = вҲ“2В·[q_err(1:3)]
att_gain = 0.5В·dt_update_avg / time_delay       # keeps damping вүҲ 0.7 across varying delay
_delta_angle_corr = Оҙa В· att_gain               # fed back into the forward step above
vel_gain = dt/clamp(_vel_tau, dt, 10);  pos_gain = dt/clamp(_pos_tau, dt, 10)
vel_corr = vel_errВ·vel_gain + ОЈvel_errВ·vel_gainВІВ·0.1     # PD, ~5% overshoot
pos_corr = pos_errВ·pos_gain + ОЈpos_errВ·pos_gainВІВ·0.1
вҶ’ applyCorrectionToOutputBuffer(vel_corr, pos_corr)      # constant correction across history
```
`_vel_tau`/`_pos_tau` are set by `EKF2_TAU_VEL` / `EKF2_TAU_POS` (both 0.25 s). `getOutputTrackingError()` (angle/vel/pos) is published in `estimator_status`.

