## 8. EKF selector & runtime noise adaptation

![EKF2Selector scoring and failover](ekf2_estimator_pipeline_2026-05-25_selector.svg)

### 8.1 EKF2Selector (`EKF2Selector.cpp`)

In multi-EKF builds, one EKF2 instance runs per IMU/mag set; the selector promotes one to publish the system topics.

- **IMU fault accumulators** (`UpdateErrorScores`, `:151`): per sensor, `ОЈ(inconsistency вҲ’ threshold)В·dt` for gyro (threshold `EKF2_SEL_IMU_RAT` 7В°/s; fault if accumulation > `EKF2_SEL_IMU_ANG` 15В°) and accel (`EKF2_SEL_IMU_ACC` 1 m/sВІ; fault if > `EKF2_SEL_IMU_VEL` 2 m/s).
- **Per-instance score** (`:298-356`): `combined_test_ratio = max(ВҪ(vel_tr + pos_tr), hgt_tr)`; `relative_test_ratio += (combined_i вҲ’ combined_selected)` clamped to Вұ1; `healthy = (no fault) & combined>0`; `warning = combined вүҘ 1`.
- **Selection / failover** (`SelectInstance`, `:114`): a health hysteresis (~1 s); switch to a better instance once it wins by `EKF2_SEL_ERR_RED` (0.2); **instant** switch on IMU fault or timeout; relative scores reset on a switch. The winner republishes `vehicle_attitude/local_position/global_position/odometry/wind` and `sensor_selection`; `estimator_selector_status` reports the scores. Single-EKF builds skip all this and publish directly.

